README for simpleElementExample
-------------------------------

The simpleElementExample provides a number of examples for using SST core.
Start with the scripts in the tests/ directory. Each script lists the relevant
implementation files in this directory as well as the expected output in the tests/refFiles directory.

Each component header in this directory additionally has a comment indicating what concepts it covers.


First Concepts
-------------------------------
- example0          : Parameter parsing, sending an event, clocks, ending simulation
- example1          : Random number generators, statistics


Basic Concepts
-------------------------------
- basicClocks       : Clocks, clock handlers, time converters, UnitAlgebra for error checking
- basicLinks        : Event handlers, multiple links, optional ports, polling links, port vectors
- basicParams       : Parsing different parameter types, UnitAlgebra, parameter arrays, required and
                      default parameter values
- basicStatistics0  : C++: Statistic types, statistics with SubIDs, obtaining multiple pointers to the same statistic
                      Python: Print statistics with various output formats (CSV, string, etc.)
- basicStatistics1  : C++: Statistic types, statistics with SubIDs, obtaining multiple pointers to the same statistic
                      Python: Selecting which statistics are generated, controlling frequency of statistic generation
- basicStatistics2  : C++: Statistic types, statistics with SubIDs, obtaining multiple pointers to the same statistic
                      Python: Controlling the type of generated statistics (histogram, accumulator, etc.)
- basicSimLifeCycle : C++: Component interaction with the SST simulation lifecycle
                      Command line: SST signal handling (SIGTERM, SIGINT, SIGUSR1, SIGUSR2)
- basicSubComponent : C++: Defining subcomponents, loading subcomponents, ELI for subcomponents
                      Python: Declaring and parameterizing user subcomponents

